**ESP-32 First-Time Setup (Arduino IDE):**

**Step 1: Install ESP-32 Board Support**

1. Open Arduino IDE
2. Go to **File â†’ Preferences**
3. In "Additional Board Manager URLs" paste:
   ```
   https://raw.githubusercontent.com/espressif/arduino-esp32/gh-pages/package_esp32_index.json
   ```
4. Click OK
5. Go to **Tools â†’ Board â†’ Boards Manager**
6. Search "ESP32"
7. Install **"ESP32 by Espressif Systems"** (takes a minute)

**Step 2: Select Board**

1. **Tools â†’ Board â†’ ESP32 Arduino â†’ "ESP32 Dev Module"**

**Step 3: Connect & Select Port**

1. Plug ESP-32 into computer via USB
2. **Tools â†’ Port** â†’ select the new COM port (Windows) or /dev/ttyUSB0 (Linux/Mac)

**Step 4: Upload Code**

